1
00:00:00,470 --> 00:00:02,310
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:02,310 --> 00:00:03,740
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:04,910 --> 00:00:07,250
Are you the only one working?
I work, too.

4
00:00:07,350 --> 00:00:08,850
I'm exhausted, too.

5
00:00:09,110 --> 00:00:11,650
Please.
For the pathetic amount you make?

6
00:00:11,680 --> 00:00:15,220
You dump the housework and our kid
on Mom and do whatever you want.

7
00:00:15,320 --> 00:00:16,490
Let's just drop it.

8
00:00:16,860 --> 00:00:19,620
I was a fool
to marry someone like you.

9
00:00:19,690 --> 00:00:23,330
Fine, then let's call it quits.
Let's get a divorce. Right now!

10
00:00:25,860 --> 00:00:27,570
Wow, that's really intense.

11
00:00:27,930 --> 00:00:30,200
Dr. Han Seong Mi,
what's your take on that?

12
00:00:30,670 --> 00:00:33,740
Yes. According to the research
of Dr. John Gottman,

13
00:00:33,810 --> 00:00:35,970
a world-renowned couples therapist,

14
00:00:36,510 --> 00:00:39,440
criticism, contempt, defensiveness,
and stonewalling...

15
00:00:39,710 --> 00:00:43,580
are four major factors
that destroy a relationship.

16
00:00:44,750 --> 00:00:46,950
Unfortunately,
the couple we just saw...

17
00:00:47,020 --> 00:00:49,920
is engaging in these kinds of
dysfunctional communication habits.

18
00:00:50,520 --> 00:00:53,890
So that's why the more they talk,
the more emotional they get,

19
00:00:54,030 --> 00:00:56,130
and the deeper
their conflict becomes.

20
00:00:56,930 --> 00:01:01,130
In that case,
what's the solution for this family?

21
00:01:01,470 --> 00:01:05,570
What this family needs most of all
is to repair their relationship.

22
00:01:06,440 --> 00:01:09,610
And that starts with love.

23
00:01:10,280 --> 00:01:12,340
To heal a relationship
hardened by past wounds,

24
00:01:12,680 --> 00:01:15,450
and to change the way they feel
through their words and actions,

25
00:01:15,950 --> 00:01:18,850
love must always be
at the center of it all.

26
00:01:20,220 --> 00:01:21,620
That is why today, for this couple,

27
00:01:22,890 --> 00:01:24,890
I am prescribing love.

28
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:28,760
(Episode 1)

29
00:01:33,470 --> 00:01:34,470
You're here.

30
00:01:34,930 --> 00:01:36,030
I'm not late.

31
00:01:36,270 --> 00:01:39,200
I know. I figured it was about time,
so I came out to greet you.

32
00:01:39,840 --> 00:01:41,810
Look at Mr. Big Shot
coming out to greet me.

33
00:01:42,210 --> 00:01:43,680
What is it? What do you need?

34
00:01:44,340 --> 00:01:45,440
Come, this way.

35
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:49,480
Let's talk at dinner after filming.
It's my treat for your birthday.

36
00:01:49,810 --> 00:01:53,590
- You still remember my birthday?
- Of course. You're my first love.

37
00:01:54,190 --> 00:01:55,790
I'll book a table
at your favorite crab place.

38
00:01:56,050 --> 00:01:59,090
No, thanks. It's my birthday.
I should spend it with my family.

39
00:01:59,460 --> 00:02:00,630
If it's urgent, just tell me now.

40
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:07,630
Let's do a new show.
Your own solo show.

41
00:02:08,430 --> 00:02:09,600
I don't think I can.

42
00:02:09,900 --> 00:02:12,100
My clinic schedule
is way too packed.

43
00:02:12,640 --> 00:02:13,940
I know I was scraping by...

44
00:02:13,940 --> 00:02:16,070
before my college buddy,
a broadcasting director,

45
00:02:16,140 --> 00:02:17,880
gave me a shot,
and I'm grateful to be this busy,

46
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:19,710
but I have a day job to get back to.

47
00:02:20,780 --> 00:02:22,880
All right. Let me know
if you change your mind. Anytime.

48
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:27,590
"Go Myung Hwan's Book Talk."
Today's guest...

49
00:02:28,020 --> 00:02:31,860
is someone our viewers
have been dying to meet.

50
00:02:32,220 --> 00:02:36,760
She's the author of the bestseller,
"Recipe For Love,"

51
00:02:37,100 --> 00:02:42,070
the love guru who prescribes love
to all of Korea's troubled families,

52
00:02:42,430 --> 00:02:46,770
and a board-certified psychiatrist,
Dr. Han Seong Mi.

53
00:02:47,170 --> 00:02:48,810
Welcome.

54
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:52,210
- Welcome.
- Hello.

55
00:02:52,280 --> 00:02:53,610
- Hello.
- Hello.

56
00:03:00,950 --> 00:03:04,520
Now, I'd like to ask
a more personal question.

57
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:07,930
In fact, the number one thing
our viewers want to know...

58
00:03:08,260 --> 00:03:12,130
is about your family life.

59
00:03:12,260 --> 00:03:13,430
Oh, right.

60
00:03:13,870 --> 00:03:15,700
According to my notes here,

61
00:03:15,770 --> 00:03:19,070
you and three generations
of your family...

62
00:03:19,170 --> 00:03:23,240
- live in Onjeong. Right?
- Yes, that's right.

63
00:03:23,510 --> 00:03:26,040
I live with my mother-in-law,
my children who still live at home,

64
00:03:26,110 --> 00:03:28,480
and my brother-in-law
and his wife as well.

65
00:03:28,580 --> 00:03:31,420
Wow, that's
a real multigenerational household.

66
00:03:31,650 --> 00:03:34,090
Any trouble with your mother-in-law?

67
00:03:34,190 --> 00:03:38,220
- None whatsoever. That's a fact.
- Wow, really?

68
00:03:38,690 --> 00:03:43,330
The person I look up to the most
is my mother-in-law.

69
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:46,430
Wow, what's she like?

70
00:03:46,860 --> 00:03:49,330
For starters,
she's absolutely beautiful.

71
00:03:49,870 --> 00:03:53,370
She takes such great care of herself
that whenever we go out together,

72
00:03:53,440 --> 00:03:55,970
- people ask if we're sisters.
- Oh, my.

73
00:03:56,310 --> 00:04:00,110
And on top of that,
she waltzes every morning.

74
00:04:00,310 --> 00:04:02,610
Excuse me? She waltzes?

75
00:04:04,320 --> 00:04:08,620
Yes. She and my father-in-law
used to waltz when they were young,

76
00:04:08,920 --> 00:04:13,420
and she still does it
every single day for exercise.

77
00:04:20,130 --> 00:04:24,370
In fact, she's the only reason
I'm able to have a career.

78
00:04:30,010 --> 00:04:33,080
Everyone, time to eat!

79
00:04:34,710 --> 00:04:38,850
As I'm busy, she's raised our kids
as if they were her own,

80
00:04:39,180 --> 00:04:43,220
and she manages our huge household
perfectly, all by herself.

81
00:04:43,290 --> 00:04:44,290
- Eat up.
- This looks delicious!

82
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:48,930
My mother-in-law is always
the steady center of our family.

83
00:04:49,130 --> 00:04:51,260
She's the rock
that holds us all together.

84
00:04:53,260 --> 00:04:56,270
Is your mother-in-law
a full-time homemaker?

85
00:04:56,630 --> 00:04:59,170
No, she's a pharmacist.

86
00:04:59,340 --> 00:05:01,670
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

87
00:05:01,740 --> 00:05:03,140
She works with my husband, a doctor,

88
00:05:03,140 --> 00:05:05,010
and my brother-in-law,
a physical therapist.

89
00:05:05,080 --> 00:05:07,910
- They're all in the same building.
- Thank you.

90
00:05:07,980 --> 00:05:09,850
- Take care.
- Thanks.

91
00:05:10,050 --> 00:05:12,520
I see.

92
00:05:12,980 --> 00:05:17,790
So your husband's a doctor.
His late grandfather, his father...

93
00:05:17,860 --> 00:05:19,590
and... Wait.

94
00:05:19,990 --> 00:05:22,590
Your two children
also went to med school?

95
00:05:23,390 --> 00:05:24,400
Yes.

96
00:05:24,500 --> 00:05:28,470
And your husband is an internist...
Hang on a second.

97
00:05:28,630 --> 00:05:31,400
Your face just lit up the second
we mentioned your husband.

98
00:05:31,400 --> 00:05:33,400
- It did.
- My gosh. Did it, really?

99
00:05:34,670 --> 00:05:36,810
What's your husband like?

100
00:05:38,840 --> 00:05:40,450
My husband...

101
00:05:41,280 --> 00:05:44,120
is a truly selfless
and idealistic doctor.

102
00:05:44,650 --> 00:05:47,290
You'd be so surprised
if you saw his clinic.

103
00:05:50,090 --> 00:05:52,360
- Hello. Good to see you.
- Yes, hello.

104
00:05:53,760 --> 00:05:54,930
Hello, welcome.

105
00:05:54,990 --> 00:05:57,930
It feels less like a clinic
and more like a local hangout.

106
00:06:00,970 --> 00:06:05,100
Try to bend it a little, like this.
Oh, ouch...

107
00:06:05,640 --> 00:06:08,610
This must've hurt so much
you couldn't get any sleep.

108
00:06:08,670 --> 00:06:11,040
- He's so down-to-earth and warm.
- It really hurts.

109
00:06:11,510 --> 00:06:14,910
He treats his patients like family.
No, actually...

110
00:06:14,980 --> 00:06:16,610
He treats them
like his own best friends.

111
00:06:17,820 --> 00:06:21,690
- Just roll up your pant leg a bit.
- Here, mix this with your rice.

112
00:06:22,190 --> 00:06:25,390
- Don't bring me things you sell.
- Please.

113
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:28,290
Doctor, you're the one
who helped me walk again,

114
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:30,900
and you even played matchmaker
for my granddaughter.

115
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:34,700
- Just a jar of fermented seafood.
- Honestly.

116
00:06:35,430 --> 00:06:38,100
But yours is too good.
I can't possibly say no...

117
00:06:38,270 --> 00:06:40,200
All right, thank you. I'll enjoy it.

118
00:06:41,010 --> 00:06:44,480
- Watch your step on the way out.
- I will.

119
00:06:46,380 --> 00:06:49,250
Mr. Go! My goodness.
What have you brought now?

120
00:06:49,310 --> 00:06:51,680
I told you. You shouldn't be
carrying heavy things.

121
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:53,550
It's some nabak kimchi.

122
00:06:54,420 --> 00:06:58,290
Your favorite.
My daughter made it for you.

123
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:03,260
Gosh, you know a meal isn't complete
for me without this.

124
00:07:03,930 --> 00:07:06,060
- Oh, boy.
- It's the best, right?

125
00:07:08,130 --> 00:07:13,040
- I really wish I could be on TV
- And he's such a romantic.

126
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:16,110
- Singing
- He likes music therapy too,

127
00:07:16,110 --> 00:07:18,140
- And dancing
- so he volunteers on weekends.

128
00:07:18,210 --> 00:07:22,310
- My pretty face
- Oh, my.

129
00:07:22,610 --> 00:07:25,650
That's what made you fall for him
and get married young.

130
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:28,750
What about your children?
You said they were med students.

131
00:07:28,820 --> 00:07:30,690
Go on and brag a little.

132
00:07:32,390 --> 00:07:36,630
Our son graduated from med school
and is now studying for his boards.

133
00:07:37,230 --> 00:07:40,260
He'll take over his dad's practice
and become a great doctor,

134
00:07:40,330 --> 00:07:43,700
making him the fourth generation
of doctors in the family.

135
00:07:45,140 --> 00:07:47,670
Is your daughter a doctor, too?

136
00:07:47,970 --> 00:07:51,480
No. She earned her medical license,

137
00:07:51,540 --> 00:07:54,080
but she felt a different calling
and is doing something else now.

138
00:07:54,150 --> 00:07:55,410
And what is it that she does?

139
00:07:56,450 --> 00:07:59,680
- Our daughter's a designer.
- A designer?

140
00:07:59,980 --> 00:08:03,890
She says that in their own way,
designers are healers, too.

141
00:08:04,660 --> 00:08:08,790
They help people's emotional health
by creating clothes that suit them.

142
00:08:09,130 --> 00:08:11,900
A "fashion therapist," if you will.

143
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:16,670
Wow. You really seem perfect.
You even raised your kids so well.

144
00:08:17,370 --> 00:08:20,710
For everyone watching at home today,
could you share your secret...

145
00:08:20,770 --> 00:08:24,180
- to raising such a perfect family?
- Of course.

146
00:08:24,940 --> 00:08:29,180
First, we respect each other,
and we don't bottle up our emotions.

147
00:08:29,780 --> 00:08:34,220
We've learned to communicate
without blaming each other.

148
00:08:34,820 --> 00:08:38,220
My, I bet every family in Korea
is envious of you.

149
00:08:38,290 --> 00:08:40,730
You're such a perfect,
exemplary family.

150
00:08:50,530 --> 00:08:53,470
Where did everyone go?
Lunch is almost over.

151
00:08:58,540 --> 00:08:59,540
You startled me!

152
00:09:00,140 --> 00:09:02,850
My goodness. What is all this?

153
00:09:02,950 --> 00:09:07,050
- Happy birthday, Dr. Han!
- Happy birthday!

154
00:09:07,750 --> 00:09:10,420
Thanks. Thank you both.

155
00:09:12,560 --> 00:09:13,560
Hold on.

156
00:09:16,260 --> 00:09:18,300
Oh, it's my husband.

157
00:09:18,800 --> 00:09:22,130
He's calling for your birthday.

158
00:09:22,130 --> 00:09:24,500
- How sweet!
- Oh, stop.

159
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:26,670
We'll get ready
for the afternoon appointments then.

160
00:09:26,670 --> 00:09:28,070
- All right. Thanks.
- All right, then.

161
00:09:28,070 --> 00:09:29,910
- Of course, happy birthday!
- Happy birthday!

162
00:09:32,340 --> 00:09:34,110
(So-called husband, Gong Jeong Han)

163
00:09:39,780 --> 00:09:40,790
What is it?

164
00:09:41,550 --> 00:09:43,190
Hey, you busy?

165
00:09:43,990 --> 00:09:44,990
Kind of. Why?

166
00:09:45,590 --> 00:09:46,760
Today...

167
00:09:47,660 --> 00:09:49,190
You know, today...

168
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:52,330
What about today? What is it?

169
00:09:52,700 --> 00:09:55,670
Well, today...
I was wondering if you...

170
00:09:56,500 --> 00:09:59,440
Spit it out. What?

171
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:00,840
No, it's just...

172
00:10:01,840 --> 00:10:03,570
I was wondering
if you could lend me some money.

173
00:10:04,740 --> 00:10:06,080
Figures.

174
00:10:07,850 --> 00:10:08,850
Hello?

175
00:10:09,810 --> 00:10:11,320
Is that why you called? For money?

176
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:12,920
What else?

177
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:14,920
You only call when you need
something, don't you?

178
00:10:15,190 --> 00:10:18,260
- So, do you have money to lend me?
- And where would I get the money?

179
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:20,290
Fine, forget it.

180
00:10:21,090 --> 00:10:22,760
Wait, what is it this time?

181
00:10:23,830 --> 00:10:25,430
You just said
you don't have any money.

182
00:10:25,700 --> 00:10:27,300
Just tell me. Now!

183
00:10:27,670 --> 00:10:31,200
The high-frequency thermotherapy
and premium AI ultrasound machines.

184
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:33,400
Are you behind on the payments?

185
00:10:33,470 --> 00:10:37,010
Yes. If I can't pay by month's end,
they're going to repossess them.

186
00:10:37,070 --> 00:10:38,780
See?

187
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:43,880
Why buy them in the first place?
For your hole-in-the-wall clinic?

188
00:10:44,250 --> 00:10:47,050
You have no idea
how amazing these are, do you?

189
00:10:47,280 --> 00:10:51,320
It has a deep-learning engine
that automatically analyzes lesions.

190
00:10:51,390 --> 00:10:53,660
How often do you use it?

191
00:10:53,660 --> 00:10:56,060
You see patients with colds,
sore knees, and backs.

192
00:10:56,230 --> 00:10:59,300
Why buy something you can't afford
if you're barely going to use it?

193
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:02,830
Hey, I saved Mr. Baek
from the hardware shop with this!

194
00:11:05,140 --> 00:11:07,340
Fine, forget it.
I'll figure it out myself.

195
00:11:07,710 --> 00:11:10,780
Figure it out how?
How are you going to solve anything?

196
00:11:11,480 --> 00:11:13,710
Take out another loan?
Go to a loan shark?

197
00:11:14,050 --> 00:11:16,050
Did you even pay your brother
this month?

198
00:11:17,480 --> 00:11:21,650
Please, just take patients
who are insured!

199
00:11:21,720 --> 00:11:23,620
And stop giving out free treatments.

200
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:25,820
How can you always be thinking
only of other people?

201
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:29,490
Are you running a charity?
When are you going to stop?

202
00:11:29,630 --> 00:11:31,900
We both know we're short on money,
so please stop causing trouble.

203
00:11:32,230 --> 00:11:33,800
Hey, but let's be honest.

204
00:11:34,130 --> 00:11:37,640
You took every last penny we had
to open your clinic in Seoul.

205
00:11:37,700 --> 00:11:39,340
That's why we're so broke
in the first place.

206
00:11:39,470 --> 00:11:43,140
I knew you'd bring that up.
Did I make that decision by myself?

207
00:11:43,210 --> 00:11:47,410
Besides, am I not paying it back?
I'm making payments every month.

208
00:11:47,550 --> 00:11:51,850
Since you're on TV more often
and seeing more patients,

209
00:11:52,080 --> 00:11:55,320
I thought you'd be making
more money, so I called.

210
00:11:55,550 --> 00:11:58,060
Between the rent for the clinic
and the rent for my studio,

211
00:11:58,120 --> 00:12:01,390
- I'm stretched thin, too.
- All right, I get it.

212
00:12:03,860 --> 00:12:05,060
For now, just try to buy some time.

213
00:12:05,900 --> 00:12:08,230
I'll come down this weekend,
and we can talk about it then.

214
00:12:08,830 --> 00:12:10,400
You're coming home this weekend?

215
00:12:11,670 --> 00:12:12,670
You don't want me to?

216
00:12:12,740 --> 00:12:17,640
No, it's just you haven't been home
in two months. Why so suddenly?

217
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:20,850
Grandfather's memorial service is
this week.

218
00:12:21,210 --> 00:12:22,610
Oh, right. The service.

219
00:12:22,910 --> 00:12:26,850
You only care about other people.
You couldn't care less about home.

220
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:29,450
Hello. Yes. I have to go.

221
00:12:29,750 --> 00:12:30,820
Hello...

222
00:12:38,530 --> 00:12:41,530
Love must always be
at the center of it all.

223
00:12:42,630 --> 00:12:44,340
That is why today, for this couple,

224
00:12:45,400 --> 00:12:47,570
I am prescribing love.

225
00:12:48,270 --> 00:12:50,270
Love... What a joke.

226
00:12:56,380 --> 00:12:58,180
(Song Jae Geun)

227
00:12:59,020 --> 00:13:02,120
So, have you decided
to give it a shot, Doctor?

228
00:13:02,520 --> 00:13:05,560
Yes. I talked it over
with my husband,

229
00:13:05,890 --> 00:13:07,990
and he thought
I should give it a shot.

230
00:13:08,890 --> 00:13:12,430
And since you're saying I'm needed,
I'd like to be helpful if I can.

231
00:13:13,900 --> 00:13:16,600
Great. You're a true doctor couple,
just as I thought.

232
00:13:17,330 --> 00:13:22,170
- Great decision. Thank you.
- But I do have one question.

233
00:13:23,270 --> 00:13:27,550
Hosting a show under my own name
is different from being a panelist.

234
00:13:28,180 --> 00:13:31,350
I was wondering about the fee
and payment structure.

235
00:13:32,250 --> 00:13:33,350
Here.

236
00:13:34,790 --> 00:13:38,220
Wow, the rice is perfect today.
Who made it?

237
00:13:38,560 --> 00:13:42,830
Yong Tae's grandmother did.
Jeong Ah brought the greens.

238
00:13:43,090 --> 00:13:46,230
- We have nabak kimchi and seafood.
- Oh, my.

239
00:13:46,300 --> 00:13:49,770
Oh, yes! Nabak kimchi from Mr. Go.
It's the absolute best!

240
00:13:50,070 --> 00:13:52,440
Oh, Mom. About Mr. Go...

241
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:54,070
He picked up his medicine, right?

242
00:13:54,140 --> 00:13:58,840
Yes. But you said he needed to make
a hospital appointment? Why?

243
00:13:59,140 --> 00:14:01,450
I'm just a little worried
about a potential heart attack.

244
00:14:02,010 --> 00:14:05,520
Oh, right. Ju Ah's mom
is coming home this weekend.

245
00:14:05,920 --> 00:14:08,820
My gosh, you actually called her?

246
00:14:09,650 --> 00:14:12,420
What's the occasion?
I didn't even have to remind you.

247
00:14:12,920 --> 00:14:13,920
Remind me of what?

248
00:14:14,460 --> 00:14:16,260
It's her birthday today.

249
00:14:17,960 --> 00:14:20,300
It's her birthday today?

250
00:14:20,730 --> 00:14:23,470
- You called her without knowing?
- Of course, he didn't know.

251
00:14:24,570 --> 00:14:26,200
Then why did you call?

252
00:14:27,140 --> 00:14:28,740
Well, I just...

253
00:14:29,840 --> 00:14:30,940
Why do you think?

254
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:34,250
Don't tell me
you asked her for money.

255
00:14:35,450 --> 00:14:39,350
I can't believe this kid...
I told you I'd take care of it.

256
00:14:39,880 --> 00:14:42,690
Why would you bother her
with a call like that?

257
00:14:43,250 --> 00:14:46,220
How would you handle it, Mom?
Where would you get the money?

258
00:14:46,590 --> 00:14:48,990
She said we'll talk again
at this weekend's memorial service.

259
00:14:49,060 --> 00:14:52,030
She's so busy. Why would she come
for the service? I can do it myself.

260
00:14:52,100 --> 00:14:55,300
Please, Mom. If she doesn't show up,
you know Uncle will make a scene.

261
00:14:55,800 --> 00:14:58,800
Mr. Gong! If you take all that,
what are we supposed to eat?

262
00:14:59,300 --> 00:15:02,110
What? Come on, there's plenty here.

263
00:15:02,370 --> 00:15:04,210
I'm taking some for Hui Gyeong.

264
00:15:04,380 --> 00:15:07,510
She's at home. She can feed herself.
Why do you dote on her so much?

265
00:15:07,580 --> 00:15:09,210
Hey, we're still
in our honeymoon phase.

266
00:15:09,210 --> 00:15:11,350
What are you talking about?
You've been married for five years.

267
00:15:11,550 --> 00:15:15,390
You're still newlyweds with no kids.
Legally, it lasts for seven years.

268
00:15:15,990 --> 00:15:20,920
Housing, tax breaks, and loans...
All of it extends to seven years.

269
00:15:21,060 --> 00:15:23,490
Sure, whatever.
Must be nice to be so lovey-dovey.

270
00:15:24,230 --> 00:15:28,400
I guess one marriage has to go well.
Dr. Gong's marriage is struggling.

271
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:32,270
I'm sorry.
I don't know what got into me.

272
00:15:33,340 --> 00:15:35,910
I wonder if Woo Jae is eating well
while he studies.

273
00:15:36,570 --> 00:15:37,880
He probably eats at the study cafe.

274
00:15:38,480 --> 00:15:41,910
But what happens now that Woo Jae
failed his medical board exam again?

275
00:15:42,510 --> 00:15:45,180
Failing once can be a simple mistake
or he was off by one row,

276
00:15:45,480 --> 00:15:48,950
but to fail both exams
two years in a row is strange.

277
00:15:49,020 --> 00:15:50,020
Don't you think?

278
00:15:53,190 --> 00:15:54,390
There I go again. I must be crazy.

279
00:15:55,660 --> 00:15:57,260
Hey, why you...

280
00:16:02,700 --> 00:16:05,470
Happy birthday to you

281
00:16:05,840 --> 00:16:08,510
Happy birthday to you

282
00:16:08,940 --> 00:16:12,940
Happy birthday, dear Mom

283
00:16:13,510 --> 00:16:16,780
Happy birthday to you

284
00:16:18,720 --> 00:16:20,780
Where are you calling from?

285
00:16:21,190 --> 00:16:22,720
I just stepped out for a minute
from studying.

286
00:16:23,020 --> 00:16:24,790
Make sure you take some breaks
and get some fresh air, Mom.

287
00:16:25,720 --> 00:16:28,330
Thank you.
You're the only one I can count on.

288
00:16:28,990 --> 00:16:31,630
Your dad just calls
to ask for money.

289
00:16:34,500 --> 00:16:36,470
I'm sorry for letting you down
this time.

290
00:16:36,970 --> 00:16:39,840
I was hoping to give you my license
for your birthday.

291
00:16:41,410 --> 00:16:42,410
Woo Jae.

292
00:16:42,940 --> 00:16:44,510
Have you thought
about a prep course?

293
00:16:45,740 --> 00:16:47,540
It's okay.
The tuition is so expensive.

294
00:16:48,250 --> 00:16:50,750
I know what I did wrong.
I'll study on my own.

295
00:16:51,820 --> 00:16:53,950
Okay.

296
00:17:03,760 --> 00:17:04,860
(Medicine, Gong Woo Jae)

297
00:17:04,930 --> 00:17:08,370
It appears to be an anxiety disorder
from extreme stress over your exams.

298
00:17:08,700 --> 00:17:13,600
I'll prescribe an antidepressant.
You should also attend therapy.

299
00:17:14,440 --> 00:17:16,310
(Hanguk University Hospital)

300
00:17:35,760 --> 00:17:38,730
- Delicious, right? It's to die for.
- Yes.

301
00:17:40,260 --> 00:17:41,530
But, honey.

302
00:17:42,070 --> 00:17:45,470
Can't you move to another clinic
that pays properly?

303
00:17:46,040 --> 00:17:49,370
No, how could I do that?
Our clinic needs a PT, too.

304
00:17:52,110 --> 00:17:56,750
But honey, what if your uncle
is hard on me at the service?

305
00:17:57,580 --> 00:17:58,980
Every time he sees me,

306
00:17:59,050 --> 00:18:02,350
he says we still don't have a child
because I'm too old.

307
00:18:02,690 --> 00:18:04,190
- Then...
- Yes?

308
00:18:04,690 --> 00:18:07,290
Why not stay late at the hair salon
and take your time coming home?

309
00:18:07,960 --> 00:18:11,130
- Really? Can I really do that?
- Of course.

310
00:18:14,130 --> 00:18:16,100
- Wait. Open wide.
- What?

311
00:18:16,300 --> 00:18:18,270
- I'm stuffed.
- Come on.

312
00:18:22,040 --> 00:18:24,340
- Then just take your time.
- Okay.

313
00:18:26,240 --> 00:18:28,310
Thanks for switching spots with me.

314
00:18:30,710 --> 00:18:34,150
I've been here for 40 years.
It's not like I'm going to run off.

315
00:18:35,020 --> 00:18:38,660
Okay, got it. All right, bye.

316
00:18:39,760 --> 00:18:41,260
Did you switch your turn
for the payout?

317
00:18:41,390 --> 00:18:42,430
Yes.

318
00:18:43,030 --> 00:18:45,630
I was in a bind, but they switched.
What a relief.

319
00:18:45,960 --> 00:18:49,030
- Oh, did you talk to Mom?
- Yes.

320
00:18:49,670 --> 00:18:52,800
Ju Ah must be swamped
with that home shopping show.

321
00:18:53,400 --> 00:18:57,040
I know. Of the two teams,
only the top one will be kept.

322
00:18:57,940 --> 00:19:00,880
So the department's being cut
in half.

323
00:19:00,980 --> 00:19:04,480
Yes. If she loses,
her entire team gets fired,

324
00:19:04,920 --> 00:19:09,350
and she'll be demoted to staff.
She's really worried.

325
00:19:09,850 --> 00:19:10,990
Yes, she must be.

326
00:19:11,690 --> 00:19:14,260
That's going to be really hard
for her to take.

327
00:19:17,230 --> 00:19:20,660
What we at FG
have been working on...

328
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:29,140
our lovingly prepared
Spring Summer collection.

329
00:19:30,710 --> 00:19:33,280
This season's concept is heritage...

330
00:19:34,080 --> 00:19:35,080
What?

331
00:19:36,780 --> 00:19:37,780
Hey!

332
00:19:38,920 --> 00:19:39,950
Eat up, then you can practice.

333
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:42,290
Gosh, seriously.

334
00:19:46,420 --> 00:19:47,460
What?

335
00:19:48,030 --> 00:19:50,830
What's this?
I'm cutting carbs for the show.

336
00:19:50,960 --> 00:19:55,600
Come on. You need carbs to be kind.
Just eat it. It won't matter.

337
00:19:56,770 --> 00:20:00,770
Why so nice, Mr. Park Jun Hyeok?
Did you forget we're rivals?

338
00:20:01,470 --> 00:20:05,910
Hey, wait. Don't tell me...
You didn't poison the food, did you?

339
00:20:06,510 --> 00:20:07,980
Can't you see I'm eating it, too?

340
00:20:12,150 --> 00:20:15,450
I really wouldn't care if I got cut
and you became the team lead.

341
00:20:15,520 --> 00:20:18,320
Hey. At least make it believable.

342
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:20,960
Was it that obvious?

343
00:20:22,330 --> 00:20:25,700
No, seriously, go easy on me, okay?
I'm the one who's desperate here.

344
00:20:25,930 --> 00:20:27,700
I mean,
both of your parents are doctors.

345
00:20:27,700 --> 00:20:30,500
You have your medical license
and were born with a silver spoon.

346
00:20:30,730 --> 00:20:33,970
Meanwhile, I don't have parents,
and I have to scrape by on my own.

347
00:20:34,970 --> 00:20:37,170
You really have no clue, do you?

348
00:20:37,540 --> 00:20:41,750
If this were a misery contest,
I'd give you a run for your money.

349
00:20:44,650 --> 00:20:45,650
Hey.

350
00:20:45,950 --> 00:20:47,850
Anyway, you seem pretty nervous.

351
00:20:48,190 --> 00:20:50,120
Your mom's a total natural
on camera, though.

352
00:20:50,350 --> 00:20:53,390
Can we not talk about my family?
I told you it was a secret.

353
00:20:54,390 --> 00:20:57,130
Honestly, though, I can see
where your mom is coming from.

354
00:20:57,560 --> 00:21:01,300
If my kid got a medical license
and then quit, I'd go crazy too.

355
00:21:02,500 --> 00:21:05,840
That's exactly when I stopped living
as my mother's daughter.

356
00:21:06,470 --> 00:21:09,970
I want to live my life as me,
Gong Ju Ah.

357
00:21:10,410 --> 00:21:14,880
Anyway, did you hear we're getting
a new director after these layoffs?

358
00:21:15,010 --> 00:21:18,820
Yes, I heard that too. They say
the new director is a foreigner.

359
00:21:19,080 --> 00:21:22,120
- From Argentina?
- Yes. What was his name again?

360
00:21:22,590 --> 00:21:25,520
Iglesias, Facu, or Ignacio?

361
00:21:25,960 --> 00:21:28,830
Iglesias or whatever.
I'll worry about that later.

362
00:21:29,860 --> 00:21:33,800
I just really want
to get through this mess.

363
00:21:34,870 --> 00:21:39,770
The more I think about it,
isn't this just too cruel?

364
00:21:39,900 --> 00:21:41,740
It's so cheap and low-down.

365
00:21:43,370 --> 00:21:46,540
Hey, what if we both just quit...

366
00:21:46,610 --> 00:21:49,510
and start our own brand together?

367
00:21:50,510 --> 00:21:53,550
It's because
you're so impulsive and reckless...

368
00:21:53,620 --> 00:21:55,720
that your mom gives you
such a hard time.

369
00:21:57,020 --> 00:21:58,260
Hey!

370
00:21:59,020 --> 00:22:01,460
Why are you always on my mom's side?

371
00:22:02,130 --> 00:22:03,230
That's ridiculous.

372
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:06,130
Grandma.

373
00:22:06,760 --> 00:22:09,000
It's your mom's birthday.
Did you call her?

374
00:22:09,670 --> 00:22:13,240
What's the big deal?
It's not like she celebrates mine.

375
00:22:13,900 --> 00:22:14,910
Still.

376
00:22:15,410 --> 00:22:17,840
That's no way to treat the mother
who gave birth to and raised you.

377
00:22:18,510 --> 00:22:21,610
Let's get that straight.
She gave birth to me,

378
00:22:21,780 --> 00:22:23,650
but you're the one
who raised me, Grandma.

379
00:22:24,850 --> 00:22:29,090
If you're late, don't bother
coming here. Go to your mom's.

380
00:22:29,650 --> 00:22:31,420
- No way.
- What?

381
00:22:31,990 --> 00:22:33,820
I'm serious. I'll lock you out
and change the door code.

382
00:22:34,420 --> 00:22:36,690
Grandma! Come on.

383
00:22:40,060 --> 00:22:41,100
Unbelievable...

384
00:22:47,370 --> 00:22:48,910
Which one can I get for you?

385
00:22:49,370 --> 00:22:52,780
No idea. The person I'm buying for
never likes anything I pick.

386
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:57,710
- Just give me the most popular one.
- And how many candles?

387
00:22:58,250 --> 00:23:00,220
One second. Let me see...

388
00:23:00,450 --> 00:23:04,450
How old is Dr. Han Seong Mi?
Is she 52 or 53?

389
00:23:07,120 --> 00:23:10,430
Just give me 5 big ones
and 5 small ones.

390
00:23:15,630 --> 00:23:18,600
What's with you? It's my birthday,
and I don't even get a single call?

391
00:23:18,670 --> 00:23:21,170
I don't care how busy you are.
You have no basic courtesy.

392
00:23:21,240 --> 00:23:22,840
How do you expect to get by
in the real world?

393
00:23:23,340 --> 00:23:25,010
Come on.

394
00:23:25,510 --> 00:23:27,340
We just really don't get along.

395
00:23:27,910 --> 00:23:29,410
We're like oil and water.

396
00:23:40,920 --> 00:23:43,560
That brat.
She left me on read again.

397
00:23:55,210 --> 00:23:56,270
Ju Ah? Is that you?

398
00:23:59,210 --> 00:24:00,210
Oh, thank you.

399
00:24:13,320 --> 00:24:15,530
To my eldest daughter,
who's always working so hard.

400
00:24:15,990 --> 00:24:18,330
I'm sorry this is all I can do
to celebrate with you.

401
00:24:19,060 --> 00:24:23,300
Happy birthday.
Thank you for being my daughter.

402
00:24:27,470 --> 00:24:28,640
Mother.

403
00:24:29,440 --> 00:24:32,640
It's just a birthday.
You shouldn't have bothered.

404
00:24:33,680 --> 00:24:35,050
I'm sorry.

405
00:24:35,550 --> 00:24:38,480
What are you sorry for?
You're always saying that.

406
00:24:39,020 --> 00:24:40,820
I heard Jeong Han called you.

407
00:24:41,850 --> 00:24:44,120
Don't worry about the money.
I've taken care of it.

408
00:24:44,420 --> 00:24:46,690
Did you ask the landlord
for the deposit back?

409
00:24:46,690 --> 00:24:48,730
Or did you dip into your savings?

410
00:24:49,760 --> 00:24:51,330
I handled it.

411
00:24:52,030 --> 00:24:55,070
Come by this weekend if you're free.
Don't rush if you're busy.

412
00:24:55,570 --> 00:25:00,500
- But I miss you so much. Just come.
- Okay, I'll be there.

413
00:25:01,400 --> 00:25:03,210
Are you feeling okay?

414
00:25:03,570 --> 00:25:07,080
Of course.
Now, eat up before it gets cold.

415
00:25:07,580 --> 00:25:10,350
If you feel lonely,
just think of me.

416
00:25:10,680 --> 00:25:15,490
- I'm the expert on being lonely.
- Okay.

417
00:25:16,250 --> 00:25:17,720
Thank you for the food, Mother.

418
00:25:29,100 --> 00:25:30,670
Oh, dear.

419
00:25:31,100 --> 00:25:34,500
I told you to sleep at your mom's.
Why did you insist on coming here?

420
00:25:34,700 --> 00:25:37,140
I'm a grown woman.
Why tell me to sleep at my mom's?

421
00:25:37,270 --> 00:25:40,280
I don't even remember sleeping
in the same room as her as a kid.

422
00:25:40,380 --> 00:25:44,210
You should've given her the cake.
Why buy it just to bring it here?

423
00:25:44,280 --> 00:25:48,450
I was going to!
I was set to surprise her with it.

424
00:25:48,550 --> 00:25:52,790
But right when I was buying it,
her text rubbed me the wrong way.

425
00:25:52,860 --> 00:25:54,660
- It just ruined the whole mood.
- Honestly.

426
00:25:54,660 --> 00:25:57,930
Yes. Are you Mr. Go Il Sik's son?

427
00:25:58,530 --> 00:26:00,960
Yes, this is Gong Jeong Han.

428
00:26:01,230 --> 00:26:03,630
Yes, from Onjeong. That's right.

429
00:26:03,800 --> 00:26:06,240
And just like that,
we're invisible again.

430
00:26:06,400 --> 00:26:09,070
He's always so nice to strangers.

431
00:26:09,510 --> 00:26:13,710
It's because of Grandfather.
If Grandfather's sick,

432
00:26:13,780 --> 00:26:17,450
he hopes someone will help him out.
So he always pays it forward.

433
00:26:17,650 --> 00:26:21,180
You mean the grandfather who ran off
30 years ago with another woman?

434
00:26:21,250 --> 00:26:24,520
- Dad's devotion is so touching.
- Ju Ah!

435
00:26:24,520 --> 00:26:25,620
What?

436
00:26:25,790 --> 00:26:30,360
She's not wrong.
Eat up and get to bed early, okay?

437
00:26:30,430 --> 00:26:32,230
- Okay.
- Good night, Grandma.

438
00:26:32,230 --> 00:26:33,300
You too.

439
00:26:37,870 --> 00:26:41,370
You must be so stress-free,
always saying what's on your mind.

440
00:26:41,500 --> 00:26:45,180
And you must never get angry,
being so understanding all the time.

441
00:26:49,280 --> 00:26:51,080
(January 30, 2026)

442
00:26:51,080 --> 00:26:52,220
My dear husband.

443
00:26:52,780 --> 00:26:54,720
It's been a while since
I've picked up a pen to write you.

444
00:26:55,990 --> 00:26:59,790
It's our eldest daughter-in-law's
53rd birthday.

445
00:27:00,860 --> 00:27:03,890
It seems like only yesterday
she married into our family at 20.

446
00:27:04,060 --> 00:27:05,930
Look how much time has passed.

447
00:27:07,300 --> 00:27:10,530
Jeong Han was struggling
to keep his clinic afloat,

448
00:27:10,700 --> 00:27:12,870
so I cashed out my savings pool
to help him.

449
00:27:13,570 --> 00:27:14,900
The seventh anniversary...

450
00:27:14,900 --> 00:27:18,410
of your father's passing
is this weekend.

451
00:27:29,750 --> 00:27:32,020
- Hello there.
- Hello.

452
00:28:02,990 --> 00:28:04,190
Gi Cheol?

453
00:28:07,320 --> 00:28:08,490
Gi Cheol!

454
00:28:13,360 --> 00:28:15,630
You're my sons' father!
Hey, Gong Gi Cheol!

455
00:28:16,500 --> 00:28:17,930
Hey, Gong Gi Cheol!

456
00:28:22,040 --> 00:28:25,410
Why pretend you don't know me?
How can you just ignore me?

457
00:28:25,940 --> 00:28:29,780
How could you do this?
How could you leave it all to me?

458
00:28:30,080 --> 00:28:34,750
You were alive all this time.
You should've called the kids.

459
00:28:35,590 --> 00:28:38,690
Who are you? Hey, what are you doing
to my husband?

460
00:28:38,920 --> 00:28:41,760
What did you just say?
Is he Gong Gi... Gong Gi Cheol?

461
00:28:42,190 --> 00:28:43,630
Let go of me.

462
00:28:46,360 --> 00:28:50,770
- Who on earth is Gong Gi Cheol?
- It's not you? It's really not you?

463
00:28:50,900 --> 00:28:53,100
I told you, he's not!
You crazy old lady!

464
00:28:54,470 --> 00:28:56,040
I'm so sorry.

465
00:28:56,110 --> 00:28:59,110
Is "sorry" meant to fix everything?
You won't get away with this!

466
00:28:59,180 --> 00:29:00,540
We're going to the police station,
right now!

467
00:29:00,540 --> 00:29:03,110
Come on.
Unbelievable. This is ridiculous.

468
00:29:03,480 --> 00:29:04,810
(Onjeong Police Substation)

469
00:29:04,810 --> 00:29:07,420
She said it was a mistake, ma'am.

470
00:29:07,550 --> 00:29:09,990
Please, for my sake, just let it go.

471
00:29:10,350 --> 00:29:13,060
But how can someone not
recognize their own husband?

472
00:29:13,120 --> 00:29:16,560
You see, her husband...

473
00:29:16,790 --> 00:29:19,730
left home 30 years ago,
so she can't recognize his face...

474
00:29:21,100 --> 00:29:25,030
Now, I see why he left.
What a crazy old bat.

475
00:29:25,100 --> 00:29:26,900
No, she's not a crazy person.

476
00:29:26,970 --> 00:29:31,740
- She's Onjeong Market's pharmacist.
- Look.

477
00:29:32,980 --> 00:29:34,780
Please come to my pharmacy.

478
00:29:34,840 --> 00:29:38,080
I'll treat your scrapes
and give you some medicine.

479
00:29:38,450 --> 00:29:40,750
Forget it.
This is just unbelievable.

480
00:29:40,950 --> 00:29:42,550
Just my luck!

481
00:29:43,050 --> 00:29:44,150
Honey, let's go.

482
00:29:44,950 --> 00:29:48,190
- Yes, thank you so much.
- All right, take care.

483
00:29:50,830 --> 00:29:52,730
- Grandma!
- Mom.

484
00:29:53,230 --> 00:29:57,570
Why did you all have to come?
Chief, I'm sorry.

485
00:29:57,670 --> 00:29:58,670
It's no trouble at all.

486
00:29:58,740 --> 00:30:02,270
I'll make sure
this never happens again.

487
00:30:03,540 --> 00:30:06,110
Mom, did you mistake someone
for Dad again?

488
00:30:08,110 --> 00:30:09,150
This time,

489
00:30:09,880 --> 00:30:11,780
I was so sure it was your father.

490
00:30:12,480 --> 00:30:15,590
Everything's been smoothed over.
You should take her home now.

491
00:30:18,190 --> 00:30:19,920
Okay, head on home.

492
00:30:24,790 --> 00:30:27,930
My goodness, Mom.
You've really taken it up a notch.

493
00:30:28,100 --> 00:30:30,100
I know your grudge against Dad,
but why did you hit the guy?

494
00:30:30,100 --> 00:30:31,430
And you choked him, too? Why?

495
00:30:32,370 --> 00:30:33,970
Just be quiet, and let's go.

496
00:30:35,140 --> 00:30:37,740
Grandma, from now on,
let's go on your walks together.

497
00:30:38,340 --> 00:30:39,540
Forget it.

498
00:30:43,810 --> 00:30:45,180
(Police)

499
00:30:48,480 --> 00:30:50,520
- Chief?
- Yes?

500
00:30:50,550 --> 00:30:53,760
What about him leaving 30 years ago?
He just ran away?

501
00:30:53,820 --> 00:30:57,030
No, wait. After that long,
wouldn't he be a missing person?

502
00:30:57,330 --> 00:31:00,330
You're new here,
so you wouldn't know the story.

503
00:31:00,860 --> 00:31:01,860
What's the story?

504
00:31:02,400 --> 00:31:04,770
- It's complicated.
- Come on. What is it?

505
00:31:05,300 --> 00:31:07,170
I get it.
They must've had a bad fight.

506
00:31:07,240 --> 00:31:10,210
Now that you're in Onjeong,
you'll find out soon enough.

507
00:31:10,610 --> 00:31:11,810
Just go on patrol.

508
00:31:12,110 --> 00:31:13,440
Yes, sir.

509
00:31:15,650 --> 00:31:17,180
Man, what was that about?

510
00:31:17,250 --> 00:31:18,780
(Onjeong Market)

511
00:31:18,850 --> 00:31:20,580
(Onjeong Market
Merchants' Association)

512
00:31:27,690 --> 00:31:30,460
Like I said, give her a refund.

513
00:31:30,530 --> 00:31:32,730
- I already told you I can't.
- Good grief.

514
00:31:32,860 --> 00:31:36,170
And why not?
This is completely ridiculous!

515
00:31:36,470 --> 00:31:37,530
Give me a break.

516
00:31:38,070 --> 00:31:41,200
Director Yang Dong Ik
of the Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic.

517
00:31:41,600 --> 00:31:43,210
Give her the refund, please.

518
00:31:43,210 --> 00:31:45,610
Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic's
Director Gong Jeong Han.

519
00:31:46,140 --> 00:31:48,340
That's not very fair of you.
No refund.

520
00:31:48,410 --> 00:31:51,580
For goodness' sake.
I keep saying I'm fine.

521
00:31:51,650 --> 00:31:55,890
See? She says she's fine.
Why butt in and demand a refund?

522
00:31:56,250 --> 00:31:59,660
Practice with a conscience for once,
will you?

523
00:32:00,060 --> 00:32:01,290
This old woman collects cardboard
to get by.

524
00:32:01,560 --> 00:32:03,760
You charged her
380 dollars for medicine?

525
00:32:03,760 --> 00:32:05,160
That's just unconscionable.

526
00:32:05,230 --> 00:32:07,900
She came in sick, I examined her,
and I wrote a prescription.

527
00:32:08,160 --> 00:32:10,170
The patient agreed to it,
so what's the problem?

528
00:32:10,230 --> 00:32:13,840
- Goodness, I did agree to it.
- But...

529
00:32:13,900 --> 00:32:18,170
- Please, don't fight.
- She said you hid the details.

530
00:32:18,880 --> 00:32:22,580
That's because she has poor eyesight
from diabetes, so it was pointless.

531
00:32:22,680 --> 00:32:24,450
You still should've asked.

532
00:32:24,750 --> 00:32:25,920
Why don't you stay out of this?

533
00:32:26,120 --> 00:32:30,850
- "You?" What's with the attitude?
- What? Attitude?

534
00:32:31,390 --> 00:32:35,060
- Hey, Gong Dae Han!
- "Hey?" Did you just call me "hey?"

535
00:32:35,120 --> 00:32:36,290
- Anyway...
- Yes, I said "hey."

536
00:32:36,360 --> 00:32:37,990
- "Hey?" Really?
- You call this practicing medicine?

537
00:32:38,060 --> 00:32:40,000
- Hey! You get over here!
- What's your problem?

538
00:32:40,060 --> 00:32:44,530
- Get lost.
- How many others did you rip off?

539
00:32:44,570 --> 00:32:47,000
- You're a total crook.
- Hey! How dare you...

540
00:32:47,070 --> 00:32:49,570
- What are you, a thug?
- What? Have you lost your mind?

541
00:32:49,640 --> 00:32:53,740
- Are you a gangster making threats?
- Whatever.

542
00:32:54,380 --> 00:32:56,250
How much money
do you think you can make like this?

543
00:32:56,310 --> 00:32:59,150
- What are you, a thug?
- What? Have you lost your mind?

544
00:32:59,150 --> 00:33:00,380
- Are you a gangster making threats?
- Whatever.

545
00:33:00,380 --> 00:33:02,490
- I can't with this guy.
- Just go.

546
00:33:02,490 --> 00:33:03,850
What's all this commotion about?

547
00:33:04,450 --> 00:33:06,860
- Get lost!
- What? Wait a minute.

548
00:33:07,290 --> 00:33:11,430
- Weren't they at the substation?
- Hey!

549
00:33:11,830 --> 00:33:13,030
You don't need to break it up.

550
00:33:13,560 --> 00:33:14,560
What?

551
00:33:15,060 --> 00:33:17,170
You must be the new officer,
so you probably don't know.

552
00:33:17,570 --> 00:33:21,500
Those two families always fight.
It's childish, so leave them be.

553
00:33:21,570 --> 00:33:23,110
But why?

554
00:33:23,440 --> 00:33:26,010
That's it. I've had enough!
Give her the refund now!

555
00:33:26,080 --> 00:33:30,180
- You're shameless! This medicine...
- What? Seriously?

556
00:33:33,320 --> 00:33:36,920
- I said give her a refund, now!
- I said no! I won't say it again.

557
00:33:38,050 --> 00:33:42,020
That's enough! I've had it!
I'm leaving! Just let me go!

558
00:33:42,090 --> 00:33:44,790
No, ma'am, wait!
Get your refund first, Ms. Park!

559
00:33:47,330 --> 00:33:50,230
- What?
- You darn punk.

560
00:33:50,730 --> 00:33:54,340
- Did you just call me a punk?
- Yes, I did. So what?

561
00:33:54,470 --> 00:33:56,840
Did you just call him a punk?
Don't cross the line.

562
00:33:56,910 --> 00:33:58,640
You're the ones
who crossed the line first.

563
00:33:58,640 --> 00:34:00,340
- Why is everyone acting like this?
- Hey!

564
00:34:01,040 --> 00:34:04,210
You take the hard-earned money
from people on public assistance...

565
00:34:04,280 --> 00:34:07,750
just to remodel your clinic,
you money-grubbing snob.

566
00:34:07,820 --> 00:34:11,150
Playing the righteous doctor
while your clinic is going under?

567
00:34:11,220 --> 00:34:13,890
You still act all high and mighty!
You hypocrite!

568
00:34:14,690 --> 00:34:18,800
You're just a flashy, noisy Bucket.

569
00:34:19,060 --> 00:34:22,500
Hey! I told you
not to call me "Bucket," didn't I?

570
00:34:22,970 --> 00:34:25,100
My name is Yang Dong Ik!

571
00:34:25,170 --> 00:34:28,440
Bucket. Clang, clang, clang. Bucket!

572
00:34:28,440 --> 00:34:30,240
- Will you shut your mouth?
- Bucket.

573
00:34:30,310 --> 00:34:33,840
- I said, my name is Yang Dong Ik!
- Clang, clang, Bucket.

574
00:34:33,840 --> 00:34:35,710
- Bucket. Oh, no!
- My gosh.

575
00:34:35,710 --> 00:34:38,280
- Dad!
- Dad, my clothes got all wet.

576
00:34:38,350 --> 00:34:39,350
Stop it!

577
00:34:40,880 --> 00:34:43,320
Man, my pants are soaked.
Good grief.

578
00:34:46,620 --> 00:34:48,790
- That son of a...
- Bye, Bucket.

579
00:35:00,540 --> 00:35:01,640
So that's what this is.

580
00:35:02,100 --> 00:35:05,240
The wife of the grandfather
from this clinic...

581
00:35:05,710 --> 00:35:09,180
and the husband of the grandmother
who's the hospital's pharmacist...

582
00:35:09,480 --> 00:35:11,810
They fell for each other and ran off
in the middle of the night.

583
00:35:12,110 --> 00:35:13,120
Thirty years ago.

584
00:35:13,480 --> 00:35:17,820
So that's why their kids are always
at each other's throats.

585
00:35:17,990 --> 00:35:21,760
There's a lot more to it than that.
You'll find out in due time.

586
00:35:22,460 --> 00:35:24,990
They're famous in this market
for being sworn enemies.

587
00:35:25,330 --> 00:35:26,460
I see.

588
00:35:27,160 --> 00:35:29,130
Famous sworn enemies.

589
00:35:30,300 --> 00:35:32,340
- Can I take a look?
- No, you can't.

590
00:35:33,640 --> 00:35:37,710
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

591
00:35:37,710 --> 00:35:39,510
(Pharmacy)

592
00:35:46,950 --> 00:35:50,650
Why is he always so extra?
Who does he think he is, so nosy?

593
00:35:50,920 --> 00:35:53,160
Is he taking herbal medicine
behind my back or something?

594
00:35:53,420 --> 00:35:55,060
Has he been drinking human blood
like a vampire?

595
00:35:55,790 --> 00:35:57,360
He never ages,
and he's so full of energy.

596
00:35:58,690 --> 00:36:01,530
I know. I keep saying we should move
the clinic to the apartment complex.

597
00:36:01,830 --> 00:36:04,900
Why did we waste all this money
on remodeling?

598
00:36:05,070 --> 00:36:07,840
As if a high-end clinic like this
can survive in a traditional market.

599
00:36:07,900 --> 00:36:10,010
You know
Dad is dead set against moving.

600
00:36:15,380 --> 00:36:18,450
Your wife went to the clinic heads'
wives' meeting, didn't she?

601
00:36:18,680 --> 00:36:21,080
I know. I'm just making sure
that's really where she went.

602
00:36:21,550 --> 00:36:24,350
She's been with us for over
15 years. You still suspect her?

603
00:36:24,950 --> 00:36:29,430
Afraid she'll leave with someone,
like our mom or Eun Bin's mom did?

604
00:36:31,890 --> 00:36:34,930
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

605
00:36:41,240 --> 00:36:43,910
- Where are you? Send a proof shot.
- This is delicious.

606
00:36:43,970 --> 00:36:46,710
- It's delicious and so clean.
- Really?

607
00:36:46,780 --> 00:36:49,880
- I'll bring the kids next time.
- You should.

608
00:36:52,650 --> 00:36:54,120
- It tastes so simple and clean.
- Isn't it so good?

609
00:36:55,420 --> 00:36:56,450
This is so good.

610
00:36:59,260 --> 00:37:02,830
My husband recently got an offer
to franchise his clinic,

611
00:37:03,160 --> 00:37:07,560
- and I'm not sure what to do.
- What's to think about? Look at us.

612
00:37:07,660 --> 00:37:09,830
The moment we changed our sign,
our bookings doubled.

613
00:37:10,230 --> 00:37:12,270
You can't underestimate
brand recognition.

614
00:37:13,670 --> 00:37:14,970
What about you guys? Not interested?

615
00:37:15,670 --> 00:37:19,440
It must be tough
with the regulars out in the sticks.

616
00:37:19,910 --> 00:37:21,480
It's not tough at all.

617
00:37:22,210 --> 00:37:24,650
We actually just expanded.

618
00:37:26,720 --> 00:37:30,520
We're having a grand reopening.
Please come by if you have time.

619
00:37:36,560 --> 00:37:38,190
Oh, so this is why
you wanted to get together.

620
00:37:40,000 --> 00:37:41,900
By the way, did you get
something done to your face?

621
00:37:45,500 --> 00:37:47,840
You know I was blessed
with natural beauty.

622
00:37:48,440 --> 00:37:52,880
I guess you forgot I was crowned
Miss Dolsan Gat Kimchi.

623
00:37:53,680 --> 00:37:54,980
That's right. You were.

624
00:37:55,280 --> 00:37:58,950
And you met Director Yang
when he judged the pageant, right?

625
00:37:59,480 --> 00:38:02,180
Yes. Oh, my dear husband.

626
00:38:02,490 --> 00:38:05,190
I'm the one who made the first move
and snagged him, you know.

627
00:38:07,560 --> 00:38:09,130
But every time I see you,

628
00:38:09,330 --> 00:38:12,860
you're decked out from head to toe
in designer brands.

629
00:38:14,000 --> 00:38:15,900
With the money my husband
works himself to the bone for,

630
00:38:16,330 --> 00:38:18,100
I feel bad about buying
even a pair of socks.

631
00:38:20,000 --> 00:38:24,170
Me, buy this?
My husband buys it all for me.

632
00:38:25,680 --> 00:38:29,750
I guess that's the perk of being
the second wife to a rich man.

633
00:38:29,810 --> 00:38:30,810
You've got to enjoy it...

634
00:38:31,810 --> 00:38:33,250
Oh, sorry.

635
00:38:33,820 --> 00:38:35,620
That just came out with no filter.

636
00:38:38,850 --> 00:38:39,920
It's because you're old.

637
00:38:40,420 --> 00:38:44,430
They say when you get old,
you just say whatever comes to mind.

638
00:38:47,930 --> 00:38:48,930
Please, eat.

639
00:38:53,670 --> 00:38:56,370
Yes, hello.
Did you check the photo I sent?

640
00:38:57,310 --> 00:39:00,080
Look, I specifically requested
a brand-new item.

641
00:39:00,280 --> 00:39:04,410
It's unacceptable for the bag
to be scratched up like this.

642
00:39:05,050 --> 00:39:08,020
I was too busy to return it,
so I just used it this time.

643
00:39:08,480 --> 00:39:11,420
But if this happens next time,
I'm taking my business elsewhere.

644
00:39:15,090 --> 00:39:16,090
What?

645
00:39:16,630 --> 00:39:17,960
Eun Bin, what are you doing?

646
00:39:18,490 --> 00:39:20,900
Can't you tell?
I'm packing a lunchbox.

647
00:39:21,260 --> 00:39:23,270
I know,
but why are you the one packing it?

648
00:39:23,800 --> 00:39:25,100
I'm taking it to someone.

649
00:39:25,400 --> 00:39:26,400
Who?

650
00:39:26,700 --> 00:39:30,670
It's not like you'd know them.
Why do you keep asking? So annoying.

651
00:39:30,740 --> 00:39:31,870
Seriously...

652
00:39:32,580 --> 00:39:35,540
- Hey! Where are the beef patties?
- The patties? You ate them.

653
00:39:35,610 --> 00:39:36,810
What, they're all gone?

654
00:39:37,180 --> 00:39:40,580
- Why?
- Don't ask why. Just make more.

655
00:39:40,680 --> 00:39:42,490
Make what? You want me to make
beef patties now?

656
00:39:42,720 --> 00:39:45,520
Why are you making me repeat myself?

657
00:39:46,790 --> 00:39:51,630
- Fine, I'll make them. Just wait.
- Seriously. Make three.

658
00:39:52,260 --> 00:39:55,500
Gosh, that's a lot. You'll get fat.
What if you get a double chin?

659
00:39:55,560 --> 00:39:59,000
I told you! They're not for me!
Gosh, seriously.

660
00:39:59,070 --> 00:40:01,600
Okay, fine.
I'll make them. Just wait.

661
00:40:01,970 --> 00:40:04,910
Why can't you just do what I ask?
You talk so much. It's so annoying.

662
00:40:05,010 --> 00:40:06,940
- All right.
- Stop touching my face!

663
00:40:07,340 --> 00:40:08,340
Seriously...

664
00:40:11,780 --> 00:40:12,780
Unbelievable.

665
00:40:20,490 --> 00:40:21,490
Woo Jae!

666
00:40:22,930 --> 00:40:23,990
What is it now?

667
00:40:26,730 --> 00:40:27,830
Ta-da!

668
00:40:29,930 --> 00:40:33,900
- What are you doing?
- You're studying for your boards,

669
00:40:33,970 --> 00:40:36,740
so I'm playing
the devoted girlfriend.

670
00:40:37,210 --> 00:40:38,840
But I'm not your boyfriend.

671
00:40:38,910 --> 00:40:41,940
Try these short rib patties.
They're amazing.

672
00:40:42,010 --> 00:40:44,580
If our grandparents and parents
found out about this,

673
00:40:44,650 --> 00:40:46,720
they'd all have a heart attack.

674
00:40:46,780 --> 00:40:47,850
Exactly.

675
00:40:48,220 --> 00:40:52,020
Doesn't that make our story tragic?
We're just like Romeo and Juliet.

676
00:40:52,090 --> 00:40:54,690
That only works
if Romeo actually loves Juliet.

677
00:40:55,690 --> 00:40:59,260
Eun Bin, I've told you.
I only see you as a little sister.

678
00:40:59,330 --> 00:41:03,930
Come on, you're just pushing me away
because you can't date right now.

679
00:41:04,030 --> 00:41:07,600
Besides, our families' feud
is our parents' business.

680
00:41:07,670 --> 00:41:11,310
If your grandfather catches you,
he'll rip all your hair out.

681
00:41:13,640 --> 00:41:14,640
He wouldn't.

682
00:41:20,980 --> 00:41:23,190
Father,
shouldn't you have some lunch?

683
00:41:23,520 --> 00:41:24,550
Forget it!

684
00:41:25,090 --> 00:41:28,490
Even if you have no appetite,
have a bite so you don't waste away.

685
00:41:28,860 --> 00:41:33,400
If I waste away, I'll die. So what?
Why live any longer at my age?

686
00:41:33,860 --> 00:41:37,230
Please don't say that. Come on out
when you get hungry, okay?

687
00:41:37,300 --> 00:41:39,000
No, I said I don't want any!

688
00:42:02,390 --> 00:42:05,190
Dad has a closet full of snacks.
You know that.

689
00:42:05,790 --> 00:42:08,900
I know, but he only eats junk food.

690
00:42:09,130 --> 00:42:12,200
I swapped them for healthy ones,
and he yelled at me so much.

691
00:42:12,570 --> 00:42:14,900
He threw a huge fit,
and then went to the market...

692
00:42:14,970 --> 00:42:16,540
and restocked it
with all sorts of junk again.

693
00:42:20,580 --> 00:42:21,580
Aren't you going to eat?

694
00:42:22,580 --> 00:42:24,150
I already had brunch, remember?

695
00:42:24,650 --> 00:42:25,780
Right.

696
00:42:26,380 --> 00:42:30,790
So that's why there's no good food.
You already had something nice.

697
00:42:31,090 --> 00:42:32,150
What? There's no good food?

698
00:42:32,520 --> 00:42:33,960
You've practically
licked the plates clean.

699
00:42:34,760 --> 00:42:37,860
And I thought
you were always on a diet.

700
00:42:37,930 --> 00:42:39,530
You call what you just ate a diet?

701
00:42:39,530 --> 00:42:40,930
You love salt,
and you eat too much and too late.

702
00:42:41,430 --> 00:42:44,200
You'll never lose the weight
if you keep eating like that.

703
00:42:45,200 --> 00:42:49,310
Can we eat out for lunch sometimes?
Must you always come home to eat?

704
00:42:50,040 --> 00:42:51,110
Why? The clinic is
just around the corner.

705
00:42:51,210 --> 00:42:52,980
Please.
You just come home to check on her.

706
00:42:53,380 --> 00:42:54,410
What? I'm not checking up on her.

707
00:42:54,780 --> 00:42:58,150
All couples do this. Didn't you know
they all use tracking apps now?

708
00:42:58,580 --> 00:43:01,320
What are you talking about?
Go ask any couple on the street.

709
00:43:01,380 --> 00:43:02,380
Nobody does that.

710
00:43:03,120 --> 00:43:08,060
Who cares what other people do?
As long as it works for us.

711
00:43:09,160 --> 00:43:12,260
Right. What a perfect couple.
Live happily ever after.

712
00:43:12,930 --> 00:43:14,900
Hey, don't be like that.
You should do it, too.

713
00:43:15,360 --> 00:43:17,400
You should install a tracking app
on your husband's phone.

714
00:43:17,700 --> 00:43:20,940
He might lie about going to work
and go to an arcade, you never know.

715
00:43:22,300 --> 00:43:26,210
Tell him to stop messing around
with stocks or pyramid schemes.

716
00:43:26,680 --> 00:43:28,640
I'm kicking you both
out of this house.

717
00:43:29,350 --> 00:43:32,720
He's not like that anymore.
He's been working so hard lately.

718
00:43:33,420 --> 00:43:36,190
Fine. Save your money and move out
while you're still mooching off us.

719
00:43:36,390 --> 00:43:37,620
What do you mean, "mooching?"

720
00:43:37,950 --> 00:43:40,290
As long as our father is alive,
this is my home too.

721
00:43:40,620 --> 00:43:43,190
If you're going to stay,
at least wash your own dishes.

722
00:43:43,560 --> 00:43:44,560
You have no shame.

723
00:43:44,660 --> 00:43:48,000
I help out at the clinic,
but your wife does nothing.

724
00:43:48,130 --> 00:43:50,330
My wife doesn't just sit at home.
She does a lot around here.

725
00:43:50,770 --> 00:43:53,470
And it's not like I'm making you
work for free. I pay you a salary.

726
00:43:53,840 --> 00:43:55,470
And you don't contribute a dime
to the household expenses.

727
00:43:55,770 --> 00:43:57,370
How many years
have you been this shameless?

728
00:43:58,410 --> 00:44:02,950
Come on, honey, stop.
It's only until Hyun Bin comes back.

729
00:44:03,010 --> 00:44:05,010
They could use Hyun Bin's room
until he gets back.

730
00:44:06,220 --> 00:44:07,380
Hyun Bin is moving back?

731
00:44:08,150 --> 00:44:10,490
Did you hear from Hyun Bin?

732
00:44:11,790 --> 00:44:12,790
No.

733
00:44:14,090 --> 00:44:16,630
That kid... He's the eldest son,

734
00:44:17,090 --> 00:44:18,090
and he's past the age
to get married.

735
00:44:18,930 --> 00:44:20,100
How long will he keep
wandering around?

736
00:44:33,140 --> 00:44:36,950
(International Airport Information,
Duty Free, Customs)

737
00:45:05,510 --> 00:45:06,880
Hello, nice to meet you.

738
00:45:06,880 --> 00:45:07,880
Hi.

739
00:45:07,880 --> 00:45:10,850
- Great day to arrive in Korea.
- Yes.

740
00:45:11,480 --> 00:45:12,480
Yes.

741
00:45:19,460 --> 00:45:20,460
Please take me to this address.

742
00:45:20,820 --> 00:45:24,230
It's 298-2 Sunbok-ri, Gopyeong-eup,
Ganghwa-gun.

743
00:45:25,590 --> 00:45:26,600
Okay.

744
00:45:36,810 --> 00:45:38,340
Smells like Korea.

745
00:45:44,110 --> 00:45:47,580
I've really missed
this murky, smoggy air.

746
00:45:48,320 --> 00:45:50,750
Looks like you were away
on a long trip.

747
00:45:51,520 --> 00:45:53,620
Not a trip. I was studying abroad.

748
00:45:54,220 --> 00:45:56,590
You know Argentina?
The soccer powerhouse.

749
00:45:57,030 --> 00:45:58,030
Right, yes.

750
00:45:58,960 --> 00:46:01,130
I lived in a city called Palermo.

751
00:46:01,460 --> 00:46:04,430
It's kind of like the Beverly Hills
of Buenos Aires.

752
00:46:05,100 --> 00:46:08,700
It's a vibrant hub of fashion, art,
and fine dining.

753
00:46:08,870 --> 00:46:09,870
I see.

754
00:46:11,270 --> 00:46:13,310
I'm just back in Korea
for a little while.

755
00:46:13,740 --> 00:46:16,110
Just for about a year.
Short but intense.

756
00:46:16,850 --> 00:46:19,180
Because someone is desperately
looking for me.

757
00:46:20,820 --> 00:46:22,050
Guess who?

758
00:46:24,090 --> 00:46:25,220
Who could it be?

759
00:46:26,020 --> 00:46:27,520
I'm not telling.

760
00:46:30,760 --> 00:46:32,590
One second.

761
00:46:33,260 --> 00:46:34,260
What?

762
00:46:36,970 --> 00:46:37,970
Vice President.

763
00:46:38,400 --> 00:46:39,400
You made it?

764
00:46:40,000 --> 00:46:42,300
I'll text you the hotel address.
Get some rest.

765
00:46:42,700 --> 00:46:45,110
I'll head over after work.
Meet me in the lobby tonight.

766
00:46:45,370 --> 00:46:46,680
I have somewhere to be first.

767
00:46:46,910 --> 00:46:48,380
I'll contact you when I'm back,
okay?

768
00:46:55,750 --> 00:46:57,520
(Hwangbo Hye Su, Vice President,
Strategic Planning Division)

769
00:46:59,720 --> 00:47:02,960
(Taehan Group)

770
00:47:05,290 --> 00:47:08,060
- Who's up first today?
- Team Manager Gong Ju Ah.

771
00:47:08,730 --> 00:47:10,930
Oh, the one from medical school?

772
00:47:34,460 --> 00:47:38,430
Let's get a full shot of the outfit,
not just the coat.

773
00:47:38,460 --> 00:47:40,800
Yes, got it.
I'm getting nervous, too.

774
00:47:43,570 --> 00:47:45,700
Ms. Gong, the VP is here.

775
00:48:00,120 --> 00:48:04,020
All right, today's brand is FG
from the Taehan Group!

776
00:48:04,190 --> 00:48:05,420
And for a special treat today...

777
00:48:05,450 --> 00:48:07,360
So, she has to be number one
in sales today, or she's out, right?

778
00:48:07,820 --> 00:48:09,290
Yikes, that's so nerve-racking.

779
00:48:09,560 --> 00:48:10,560
Please welcome her.

780
00:48:11,690 --> 00:48:15,630
Yes, we at FG have poured our hearts
into preparing this SS collection,

781
00:48:15,800 --> 00:48:18,300
and I'm so happy to be able
to present it to you myself.

782
00:48:18,370 --> 00:48:20,940
Ju Ah is so photogenic.
She looks gorgeous.

783
00:48:21,170 --> 00:48:22,170
You're gorgeous, too.

784
00:48:24,070 --> 00:48:28,710
This season's concept is
"Heritage and Modernity."

785
00:48:29,650 --> 00:48:33,650
Then, why don't you tell us
about the outfit you're wearing?

786
00:48:33,820 --> 00:48:34,820
Yes, of course.

787
00:48:35,220 --> 00:48:39,350
It's a sporty look, pairing a skirt
with this very vibrant jacket.

788
00:48:39,420 --> 00:48:41,660
Wow, that's incredibly practical.

789
00:48:42,160 --> 00:48:45,290
Yes, the jacket is especially great
because it has a zipper on the side,

790
00:48:45,360 --> 00:48:47,860
which makes it incredibly easy
to put on and take off.

791
00:48:47,960 --> 00:48:51,070
Could you show us how it works?

792
00:48:51,170 --> 00:48:52,600
- Of course.
- Great.

793
00:48:52,670 --> 00:48:53,770
So you just unzip it like...

794
00:49:00,240 --> 00:49:03,210
See? It's very simple.
You just unzip it...

795
00:49:10,350 --> 00:49:11,350
What's wrong with her?

796
00:49:12,790 --> 00:49:15,020
- What's she doing?
- Oh, no.

797
00:49:22,660 --> 00:49:24,430
Just take your time and pull it up.

798
00:49:32,710 --> 00:49:33,710
Oh, my!

799
00:49:34,240 --> 00:49:36,210
Oh, no! My goodness.

800
00:49:41,050 --> 00:49:44,190
Dr. Han! You must see this!
It's a wardrobe malfunction.

801
00:49:44,250 --> 00:49:47,790
Her jacket ripped! They said
she's the team lead. My gosh.

802
00:49:47,860 --> 00:49:51,160
- How humiliating.
- Oh, no!

803
00:49:51,430 --> 00:49:54,800
- I can't watch. This is awful.
- I feel so bad for her.

804
00:49:58,430 --> 00:50:00,940
(Today's Home Shopping
Wardrobe Malfunction)

805
00:50:03,910 --> 00:50:07,240
Gosh, I'm so embarrassed
I could die.

806
00:50:08,280 --> 00:50:11,280
Wow, how am I ever
going to live this down?

807
00:50:18,790 --> 00:50:19,790
Ju Ah.

808
00:50:23,290 --> 00:50:24,360
Goodness.

809
00:50:27,900 --> 00:50:29,130
Hey, are you okay?

810
00:50:32,000 --> 00:50:34,300
Did yours go okay?

811
00:50:35,000 --> 00:50:36,170
You didn't mess up, did you?

812
00:50:38,040 --> 00:50:39,040
No.

813
00:50:39,640 --> 00:50:41,940
- I'm sorry.
- What are you sorry for?

814
00:50:44,280 --> 00:50:48,280
What am I going to do?
I think it's all over social media.

815
00:50:49,280 --> 00:50:54,020
How on earth did this even happen?
I just don't get it.

816
00:50:54,790 --> 00:50:56,090
Try not to let it get to you.

817
00:51:26,120 --> 00:51:27,160
Oh, man.

818
00:51:27,860 --> 00:51:29,160
This is killing me.

819
00:51:31,190 --> 00:51:32,730
Where the heck is he?

820
00:51:42,970 --> 00:51:44,010
Sir!

821
00:51:55,720 --> 00:51:56,720
There he is.

822
00:52:05,360 --> 00:52:06,360
Sir!

823
00:52:07,030 --> 00:52:08,030
And who might you be?

824
00:52:08,430 --> 00:52:12,070
In Episode 531 of "I Am Wild,"

825
00:52:12,470 --> 00:52:16,710
you took some winter-dried greens,
pork, baby potatoes, and carrots,

826
00:52:17,040 --> 00:52:18,910
threw them on a cast-iron lid,
and boiled them...

827
00:52:19,370 --> 00:52:21,110
to create your famous
radish green curry over rice.

828
00:52:21,480 --> 00:52:23,040
You're Mr. Bae Bong Nam, aren't you?

829
00:52:23,310 --> 00:52:24,410
Yes, I am, but...

830
00:52:25,150 --> 00:52:26,150
I can't believe it.

831
00:52:28,350 --> 00:52:29,520
It's such an honor to meet you, sir.

832
00:52:30,020 --> 00:52:31,020
Thank you.

833
00:52:34,790 --> 00:52:37,560
Thank you, Lord!

834
00:52:45,330 --> 00:52:47,170
Let me just put this over here.

835
00:52:47,740 --> 00:52:49,640
The apples go at the end...

836
00:52:50,410 --> 00:52:51,410
And over here...

837
00:52:54,210 --> 00:52:56,240
- Seon Hae.
- Yes?

838
00:52:57,350 --> 00:53:01,050
Where are the daughters-in-law?
Why are you doing all this alone?

839
00:53:01,550 --> 00:53:04,790
What do you mean alone, Uncle?
I'm here. Woo Jae, too.

840
00:53:05,220 --> 00:53:06,520
Then where's your wife?

841
00:53:07,160 --> 00:53:09,220
This is just ridiculous.

842
00:53:09,720 --> 00:53:12,230
Hui Gyeong has work.
You know she's at the salon.

843
00:53:12,490 --> 00:53:15,260
Mom will be here soon.
She's busy with work, you know.

844
00:53:16,100 --> 00:53:17,100
And Jeong Han?

845
00:53:18,000 --> 00:53:20,540
Where is the eldest son?
Why are you starting without him?

846
00:53:20,670 --> 00:53:23,840
Uncle, it's still early.
Why are you getting so worked up?

847
00:53:23,940 --> 00:53:26,840
But dear,
why isn't Hui Gyeong here yet?

848
00:53:26,910 --> 00:53:28,840
I actually told her
to come a little later.

849
00:53:29,310 --> 00:53:30,680
I'll go get her now.

850
00:53:31,480 --> 00:53:33,180
I'll go get Dad.

851
00:53:40,460 --> 00:53:42,620
- I'll be right back. You go ahead.
- Okay.

852
00:53:42,620 --> 00:53:43,830
- Dae Han.
- Seong Mi.

853
00:53:44,660 --> 00:53:45,890
Go on inside.

854
00:53:46,060 --> 00:53:49,060
Uncle's been here for a while,
making a scene, asking for everyone.

855
00:53:49,130 --> 00:53:50,130
- See you in a bit.
- Okay.

856
00:53:50,600 --> 00:53:52,630
Mom, you didn't see Dad
on your way here, did you?

857
00:53:52,730 --> 00:53:55,870
- Why? Isn't he home?
- No. I'll go get him.

858
00:53:58,840 --> 00:54:00,140
Good grief.

859
00:54:17,190 --> 00:54:19,130
Dad!

860
00:54:20,630 --> 00:54:22,400
Where could he be?
He's not even answering his phone.

861
00:54:23,870 --> 00:54:25,270
(Paramedics)

862
00:54:25,330 --> 00:54:27,640
BP's 80 over 50.
His pulse is dropping.

863
00:54:28,440 --> 00:54:31,870
It's likely a myocardial infarction.
I suspect it's the anterior wall.

864
00:54:32,070 --> 00:54:35,910
He needs a coronary angiography.
Get him to a hospital right now.

865
00:54:36,010 --> 00:54:37,250
- Got it.
- Right.

866
00:54:38,080 --> 00:54:41,680
Sir. I'm right here with you.

867
00:54:42,220 --> 00:54:44,950
We've contacted your children,
so please don't worry.

868
00:54:45,020 --> 00:54:46,790
Just try and relax.

869
00:54:51,190 --> 00:54:52,590
The person you're trying to reach
is unavailable...

870
00:54:54,260 --> 00:54:57,030
Why isn't he picking up?
Where did he go now?

871
00:55:01,870 --> 00:55:03,770
(Neungi Mushroom Chicken Soup)

872
00:55:04,570 --> 00:55:09,510
(Dr. Han Seong Mi)

873
00:55:33,540 --> 00:55:34,770
(Isulro Soju)

874
00:55:37,110 --> 00:55:38,110
Excuse me.

875
00:55:42,940 --> 00:55:44,450
(Isulro Soju)

876
00:55:47,020 --> 00:55:49,680
Sir, can we get another bottle
of soju over here?

877
00:55:51,850 --> 00:55:52,850
Excuse me?

878
00:55:53,250 --> 00:55:54,690
Soju.

879
00:55:59,990 --> 00:56:02,030
- Thanks.
- Sure.

880
00:56:07,740 --> 00:56:08,740
What is it?

881
00:56:19,610 --> 00:56:21,350
You just look really familiar.

882
00:56:21,880 --> 00:56:24,290
I doubt that.
This is my first time here.

883
00:56:24,350 --> 00:56:26,150
Yes, me too.

884
00:56:28,260 --> 00:56:29,690
You don't work here?

885
00:56:34,200 --> 00:56:35,730
I'm so sorry.

886
00:56:36,100 --> 00:56:37,270
No worries.

887
00:56:37,930 --> 00:56:38,930
But still...

888
00:56:39,770 --> 00:56:41,640
You just look so familiar.

889
00:56:44,110 --> 00:56:46,310
Did you see
that home shopping thing?

890
00:56:46,610 --> 00:56:51,080
- What?
- That viral wardrobe malfunction.

891
00:56:51,480 --> 00:56:53,010
Is that what you're thinking of?

892
00:56:53,920 --> 00:56:54,920
What?

893
00:56:59,550 --> 00:57:03,590
People are so mean.
As if they never make mistakes.

894
00:57:04,190 --> 00:57:08,230
Something like that is a disaster,
isn't it?

895
00:57:08,400 --> 00:57:10,000
When something like that happens
to someone,

896
00:57:10,060 --> 00:57:14,170
can't people just
look the other way?

897
00:57:14,240 --> 00:57:17,510
But no, they have to go
and immortalize it online,

898
00:57:17,610 --> 00:57:19,640
and tear that person down
just to get a kick out of it?

899
00:57:21,180 --> 00:57:24,850
Seriously, some people
have zero compassion.

900
00:57:25,950 --> 00:57:27,680
The person it happened to...

901
00:57:28,550 --> 00:57:32,520
could be so humiliated
they want to die, you know?

902
00:57:35,290 --> 00:57:37,390
- Right.
- So...

903
00:57:38,230 --> 00:57:41,630
please just pretend
you don't recognize me.

904
00:57:42,730 --> 00:57:44,970
You can do that much for me,
can't you?

905
00:57:46,470 --> 00:57:47,470
Okay.

906
00:58:17,370 --> 00:58:19,370
(Habi Hair Salon)

907
00:58:20,970 --> 00:58:21,970
What?

908
00:58:25,470 --> 00:58:26,980
My honey's not at the shop.

909
00:58:45,330 --> 00:58:46,900
I'm thinking of growing it out.

910
00:58:47,330 --> 00:58:50,330
- You'd look pretty either way.
- This is my hair without bangs.

911
00:59:06,980 --> 00:59:10,020
(Our Deepest Condolences)

912
00:59:26,330 --> 00:59:27,340
Wait.

913
00:59:28,100 --> 00:59:31,640
- Alone? Where's Hui Gyeong?
- What?

914
00:59:32,610 --> 00:59:35,640
Well... What about Jeong Han?
He's still not here?

915
00:59:35,710 --> 00:59:38,280
No. We can't reach him,
and he's not at the clinic.

916
00:59:38,550 --> 00:59:41,220
Forget it.
Let's just start without them.

917
01:00:22,360 --> 01:00:23,990
I'm heading out.

918
01:00:26,590 --> 01:00:30,060
Why are you leaving already?
Please wait. I packed you some food.

919
01:00:30,130 --> 01:00:31,130
There's no need.

920
01:00:32,000 --> 01:00:33,000
Oh, Jeong Han.

921
01:00:35,270 --> 01:00:36,270
Honey.

922
01:00:36,540 --> 01:00:38,470
- I'm here.
- Jeong Han.

923
01:00:38,740 --> 01:00:41,680
What took you so long?
Why didn't you answer your phone?

924
01:00:42,580 --> 01:00:44,380
Well, it's just...

925
01:00:45,910 --> 01:00:46,950
Are you...

926
01:00:47,650 --> 01:00:49,680
Have you been drinking?

927
01:00:50,920 --> 01:00:52,750
Yes, I... I had a little to drink.

928
01:00:53,350 --> 01:00:54,660
Of all the nerve...

929
01:00:54,960 --> 01:00:57,660
Now, I've seen everything.

930
01:00:58,460 --> 01:01:01,930
Seon Hae! Is this how
you raised your children?

931
01:01:02,200 --> 01:01:03,260
Uncle!

932
01:01:03,700 --> 01:01:05,930
Mom is too old for you
to be lecturing her on parenting.

933
01:01:06,070 --> 01:01:07,070
Dae Han.

934
01:01:07,370 --> 01:01:08,870
This little brat...

935
01:01:09,140 --> 01:01:10,910
You're going to
talk back to me, too?

936
01:01:11,240 --> 01:01:15,610
I'm glad I didn't bring my family.
I didn't want them to see this mess.

937
01:01:16,410 --> 01:01:20,050
So what if one's a doctor
and the other has a Ph.D.?

938
01:01:20,480 --> 01:01:24,290
This is what happens
when kids grow up without a father.

939
01:01:24,320 --> 01:01:25,790
That's not it at all.

940
01:01:26,950 --> 01:01:30,360
- What do you mean?
- He's the one who walked out on us!

941
01:01:30,390 --> 01:01:31,390
What did you say?

942
01:01:32,030 --> 01:01:34,400
What's gotten into everyone?
Stop it, all of you.

943
01:01:34,560 --> 01:01:37,170
Ever since Dad left,
Mom has been all alone.

944
01:01:37,700 --> 01:01:41,000
She cared for Grandfather
until the end, provided for us,

945
01:01:41,070 --> 01:01:43,040
and has spent her life
raising her own grandchildren.

946
01:01:43,470 --> 01:01:45,770
She endured all those years
completely on her own.

947
01:01:46,070 --> 01:01:49,140
Dad's the one who had an affair
and left home.

948
01:01:49,210 --> 01:01:53,110
- Why are you taking it out on Mom?
- Had your mother been a good wife,

949
01:01:53,480 --> 01:01:55,650
my brother never would've left
for another woman!

950
01:01:55,720 --> 01:01:59,520
Uncle! Mom, that's it.
We're not doing this memorial.

951
01:01:59,820 --> 01:02:01,790
Why hold a memorial for Grandfather
when his own son doesn't even care?

952
01:02:01,860 --> 01:02:06,330
Why should you be humiliated for it?
And another thing.

953
01:02:06,830 --> 01:02:09,060
Let's just consider our father dead.
Darn it.

954
01:02:10,060 --> 01:02:14,140
Fine. Good idea, you brat.

955
01:02:14,600 --> 01:02:17,870
You're right.
He'd be better off dead somewhere.

956
01:02:18,170 --> 01:02:22,180
If I were him,
I wouldn't visit this madhouse!

957
01:02:22,440 --> 01:02:24,910
Gosh, I can't even with this...

958
01:02:48,070 --> 01:02:49,940
Honey, I was waiting outside.

959
01:02:50,000 --> 01:02:53,270
I came in since your uncle left.
Smart, right?

960
01:02:54,610 --> 01:02:58,380
Hey. Did your uncle
make you angry, sweetie?

961
01:03:05,490 --> 01:03:08,820
Where on earth were you drinking
to show up and act like this?

962
01:03:09,390 --> 01:03:12,190
I booked an appointment
for Mr. Go at a big hospital.

963
01:03:12,560 --> 01:03:16,330
But he missed his appointment
and wasn't answering his phone.

964
01:03:16,530 --> 01:03:20,100
What are you even talking about?
Is this about a patient again?

965
01:03:20,300 --> 01:03:22,770
So I rushed over to his house
to check on him.

966
01:03:22,840 --> 01:03:25,770
And what?
Did he drop dead or something?

967
01:03:26,140 --> 01:03:28,810
You... How can you be so...

968
01:03:28,880 --> 01:03:32,380
What? What did I do?
Are you blaming me for this, too?

969
01:03:32,810 --> 01:03:34,780
Gosh, forget it.

970
01:03:35,720 --> 01:03:37,420
How could you?

971
01:03:37,690 --> 01:03:41,160
How can you just ignore your family
and do whatever you want?

972
01:03:41,360 --> 01:03:44,230
You dump everything on my mom
and live however you want, too!

973
01:03:44,960 --> 01:03:45,960
What?

974
01:03:48,560 --> 01:03:50,800
I'm so sick of you.

975
01:03:51,630 --> 01:03:53,900
Do you even know
what my life is like out there?

976
01:03:54,470 --> 01:03:57,070
Do you have any idea
what my life is like?

977
01:03:58,540 --> 01:03:59,670
I regret this so much.

978
01:04:00,370 --> 01:04:03,440
I truly regret marrying you.

979
01:04:03,810 --> 01:04:07,620
Honestly, if it weren't for Ju Ah,
I never would have married you.

980
01:04:09,020 --> 01:04:11,590
Hey, the feeling is mutual.
Darn it...

981
01:04:17,260 --> 01:04:19,230
Whenever my mom and dad fight,

982
01:04:19,490 --> 01:04:22,630
they always say the same thing.

983
01:04:24,130 --> 01:04:26,530
"If it weren't for Ju Ah,"

984
01:04:26,970 --> 01:04:29,140
"I never would've married you."

985
01:04:31,540 --> 01:04:33,670
Ever since I was a little kid.

986
01:04:34,410 --> 01:04:37,380
even if I pulled the covers
over my head...

987
01:04:37,680 --> 01:04:39,950
and plugged my ears
as tight as I could,

988
01:04:41,020 --> 01:04:42,250
those words...

989
01:04:42,650 --> 01:04:46,520
would pierce through the covers,
through my ears,

990
01:04:48,060 --> 01:04:50,490
and stab me right in the heart.

991
01:04:55,060 --> 01:04:58,470
(Gaetdali Beach)

992
01:05:05,070 --> 01:05:07,810
Gosh, what is she doing now,
worrying me like this?

993
01:05:10,240 --> 01:05:11,250
No, wait.

994
01:05:12,080 --> 01:05:13,710
She asked me
to pretend I don't know anything.

995
01:05:16,150 --> 01:05:17,320
I...

996
01:05:18,390 --> 01:05:20,860
often felt like I was someone...

997
01:05:21,360 --> 01:05:24,560
who wasn't needed in this world.

998
01:05:26,530 --> 01:05:28,400
My existence...

999
01:05:29,530 --> 01:05:34,470
wasn't the fruit of their love,
but just a mistake!

1000
01:05:37,200 --> 01:05:38,410
It was like...

1001
01:05:39,370 --> 01:05:43,410
I've spent my whole life
feeling abandoned, I guess?

1002
01:06:09,140 --> 01:06:11,610
- Stop drinking, honey.
- Leave me alone.

1003
01:06:14,810 --> 01:06:16,480
What are you so mad about?

1004
01:06:17,110 --> 01:06:18,280
We'll talk later.

1005
01:06:18,950 --> 01:06:20,110
Is something wrong?

1006
01:06:20,880 --> 01:06:21,880
No, it's nothing.

1007
01:06:22,380 --> 01:06:25,690
What is wrong with you, honey?
You're the one who said to be late.

1008
01:06:25,750 --> 01:06:27,360
Just shut up already.

1009
01:06:28,990 --> 01:06:29,990
Uncle.

1010
01:06:32,890 --> 01:06:37,160
You promised you'd treat me well
around your family if we moved in.

1011
01:06:37,600 --> 01:06:40,170
When we gave your brother
the deposit to move in here,

1012
01:06:40,870 --> 01:06:42,840
that one promise was all I had
to go on.

1013
01:06:43,900 --> 01:06:44,910
Hui Gyeong.

1014
01:06:45,710 --> 01:06:48,510
I am truly sorry about that.

1015
01:06:50,310 --> 01:06:53,010
- I'll get the money quickly and...
- Seong Mi.

1016
01:06:54,450 --> 01:06:55,820
If this is too hard for you,

1017
01:06:56,850 --> 01:06:58,490
you don't have to stay with me.

1018
01:07:01,660 --> 01:07:02,660
What?

1019
01:07:03,820 --> 01:07:05,960
- Dad?
- Hey.

1020
01:07:06,030 --> 01:07:07,130
I'm sorry, Mom.

1021
01:07:08,260 --> 01:07:09,330
Seong Mi and I...

1022
01:07:10,200 --> 01:07:11,430
We're splitting up.

1023
01:07:25,150 --> 01:07:27,350
(Special thanks to Go Myung Hwan,
Jo Seung Je, and Eom Ji In)

1024
01:07:51,210 --> 01:07:53,910
(Recipe For Love)

1025
01:07:54,010 --> 01:07:56,610
I wish I'd never been born...

1026
01:07:56,740 --> 01:07:57,750
Hey!

1027
01:07:57,750 --> 01:08:00,280
Her husband blew all their money,
so she's living with her family.

1028
01:08:01,450 --> 01:08:04,450
When your daughter's struggling,
shouldn't you be there for her?

1029
01:08:04,590 --> 01:08:07,590
You're the one who messed up.
Why are you taking it out on me?

1030
01:08:07,820 --> 01:08:09,490
- Should I do it here?
- Do what?

1031
01:08:09,560 --> 01:08:12,490
- Didn't you want my autograph?
- Gosh, how conceited.

1032
01:08:12,560 --> 01:08:15,730
- I heard that.
- When did you go to Seoul? A hotel?

1033
01:08:16,230 --> 01:08:18,100
The more I think, this is crazy.

1034
01:08:18,200 --> 01:08:19,730
Are you really getting a divorce?
